<review>I was disappointed with the lack of flavor in the breakfast sandwiches. We got the Sriracha Honey Sunrise and the Skinny Bacon Avocado & Tomato Egg White, and the hash brown cup. They look delicious, freshly made, and made quickly, but they lacked any of the strong flavors that I was expecting, particularly for the Sriracha Honey sandwich - it wasn‚Äôt spicy at all and the sweet undertones were so subtle that they were missed.

The Skinny sandwich was better, and I‚Äôd recommend that over the honey sriracha, but only because the tomato spread gives the sandwich some flavor complexity, adding a sweet smokiness to it. For the hash brown, I could take it or leave it. I was excited for the flavors included (chives, cream cheese, cheddar, etc.), but it left me unimpressed.

For the price of the sandwiches (~$7 each) and the underwhelming flavors all around, I wouldn‚Äôt recommend it.< /review><GmapID>0x80dcdef70d89379d:0x38b67d6a60bde03c< /GmapID>< Pics>

<Date>1600575014527< /Date>< Review>
I love Marco Polo and will go out of my way to go here. The ice cream tastes super fresh, and like it's made with quality ingredients. My favorite part is that they have such a wide range of flavors, especially Asian and SE Asian flavors (taro, durian, black sesame, etc.). They also offer unconventional drink combinations (like a coconut ice cream + sprite for example). Well worth the trip!</Review>

<Review>Marco Polo is a good place if you're hankering for a gelato shop with fun Asian flavors.  This location is at an edge of The Shops at Vietnam Town - the largest Vietnamese Plaza in California, or so the sign says.

I sampled nearly every fun flavor and settled upon the Thai Iced Tea and the Taro in a cup for $5.50 for two flavors, though tempted by the Banana Walnut and Lychee.  Meanwhile, a non-Asian family ordered their Double Chocolate, Mocha Chip, Vanilla, and Strawberry.  So the options are there.

Water was available against the wall - just ask for a cup.  A bathroom was tucked down the hall.  Limited seating<//Review></record></dataset><record>

<user_name>Master Maggie Li</user_name><time>1515461675876</time>< rating>
5<//rating>
< Review>
Honestly the best gelato in San Jose and maybe even in the entire Bay Area! Lots of tropical fruit flavors, and all come with real fruit inside. For fruit flavors, I particularly loved the lychee and durian. Other flavors I recommend:
-Thai iced tea, strong Thai Tea flavor
-Taro (made with taro and coconut so it's a bit grainy, the same texture of real taro. Ans it was super soft because of the coconut
-Coffe cognac, do NOT miss this if you are a coffee lover. I may or may not be biased because coffee is amongst my Top 3 favorite flavors

I cannot recommend this place enough and cannot wait to come back!!

Tip:
1) Try as many samples as you want (if not busy)
2) $10 minimum for credit cards (each small, 1-2 flavors, is $5.20)< /Review>

<rating>5< /rating><text>In A Nutshell:

-So happy that the owners decided to open a SoBay (South Bay) location.
-What I like about Marco Polo (cool name and all) is the exotic South East Asian fruit flavors (i.e. mangosteen, durian, soursop, guava, jackfruit, lychee, etc...).
-Everything about this place is simple and clean.  The layout is definitely a lot more fancier than the SF store, but I could care less as long as the ice cream still tastes the same.

Overall, as it continually trends warmer in California, I'll continually make my way to Marco Polo (and I don't even like sweets).  Grab some!</text>< pics>

< Review>
This is a large (20 acres), beautiful park serving a large variety of needs. Here you'll find a kids' playground, bbqs, softball and baseball fields, tennis and basketball courts, a skate park, and plenty of parking.  There are also restrooms.  Bbq areas can be reserved for large groups.  The park has a nice variety of mature trees.  It's the perfect place for a family outing.  The Claremont Youth Activity Center and Taylor Hall are also located here.</Review>

< Text>
After a long day of attending back to back online classes, doing Master's level coursework and presenting in graduate seminars, it's no surprise that the best part of my day is logging into TutorMe and helping high school and college students get to where I am!

Tutoring at Tutorme has probably been my most engaging experience thus far, even as comparable as tutoring in person if I do say so myself. As someone who has tutored with other platforms, nothing compares to the user-friendliness and ease of the TutorMe lesson space. And the fact that the whiteboard is interactive, gets stored after a lesson so you can access it on your own time is a huge plus!

In these times when in-person meetings have been indefinitely suspended, TutorMe proves you don't need to be physically present to properly hold a tutoring session!<//Text>

<UserId.>100253411309891942570</UserId.><username>Hannah Moody-Goo</username>< date>
1591471143583</date>
< Rating>
4< /Rating>
<Text>I've worked at TutorMe for a couple of months and have really enjoyed it thus far! The job is completely remote and flexible based on your schedule, so you can work whenever you want and as much or as little as you want. You can choose a variety of topics to tutor in and most of the students are really open and easy to work with. My position as a Virtual Librarian helps to keep up my reference interview skills while job searching and as a writing tutor, I get to help both ELL and other students with their writing skills.

The tutoring software is really easy to use, but I wish it was more customizable. There are some features related to math tutoring that aren't relevant to my tutoring and sometimes get in the way. I also wish the pay was a bit better. It is $16 an hour, but that is all dependent on which students you actually get and how long your tutoring session is. When there are too many tutors on and not enough students, it can be really difficult to claim jobs.

Overall, I really enjoy working at TutorMe! The supervisors for both the Writing Lab and the Library have been fantastic and supportive. Their training is quick and easy, but really helpful, too. I really enjoy the flexibility of working around my schedule and having the extra help. I think this is a great "side gig" that, if you are quick and dedicated, can be the main gig.<//Text>< pics>

< Review>
Good interface to connect with students as a tutor, with useful features such as screensharing, multiple whiteboards, a code editor, and Google Docs integration. All sessions also have audio and video capabilities if the student and tutor agree to use those. Can be difficult at times to obtain sessions as a tutor because they are taken very quickly, so be prepared to claim a lesson as soon as you see it even before knowing what the student needs help on. Tutors receive a standard hourly rate for tutoring that is somewhat low in comparison to what I would charge for private tutoring and also significantly lower than what students actually pay per hour; though it seems they have their hands full with complaints from students regarding pricing.<//Review>

<Date>1583265220406<//Date><Rate>4</Rate>< Text>
The most telling detail of this new (relatively) online tutoring service is their utter similarity to some of their contemporaries. And while such is a sincere imitation, the lack of fundamental updates in the form of written lessons in tandem with live sessions for the standard students makes it very difficult for revenue to be generated evenly.

To this end, I also suggest a more robust communication system, as a student following up on initial messages sent to potential tutors is the exception rather than the rule. Add in a rather apparent sampling of international students with time zone differences and actual sessions are few and far between...

Do not continue down the road of decline that is CourseHero, as your strengths are quite prominent; they just need some fine tuning. Students would likely benefit from such changes just as readily as the tutors.<//Text>

<username>Julie Caywood< /username><time>1583556066172< /time><rate>5<//rate>< Text>
You want the blunt truth? Here, let me tell you how my experience has been with TutorMe. Most of the time, you will run into companies that don't care about you as an individual and you will feel so worthless only to be left with the feeling of why work for the company. But for the 4 years I have tutored for TutorMe, I have noticed that this isn't the case at all. They become a part of your tutoring experience. Keeping you update with the latest news, payment situations, student-related issues and always open to a simple conversation. They will grow along side of you if you give them 100%. TutorMe communicates with you on a gentle yet direct approach. Sure, no company is perfect, but once you get past that idea, then you learn to just work for the pure idea of wanting to make a difference and along the way you have a company who desires to be on the same page as you. It's a share a picture of your newborn baby or roast a bag of coffee kind of relationship I have with the company. TutorMe strives to provide a positive environment for all who click onto its platform. The lesson space is easy to access and become knowledge about. The admins are efficient in answering questions.  The technology is always improving. The IT guys are working on bugs immediately when they are reported. And how do I know? I ask. I'm aware. The company wants you to be a valuable resource to its business. Love you, guys.< /Text>

An old world chocolatier, producing a wide assortment of hand-dipped morsels. The trendy shop in an historic building on Main Street Porterville has large windows to view the magic in the kitchen and cafe tables to savor your treats while you sip on a latte made with freshly ground coffee.  Try the oat milk lattes.  You can also take a bag of fresh coffee beans home, or have them grind them for you. My go to store for gifts and souvenirs. The staff is friendly and accomodating.</Text>

<Text>I have gone as many times as I could! I Get there before they open to limit my waiting time. I sometimes take a coffee and snack. <username>Andrea Duran<//username><time>1481710532956<//time>< rating>

<review>I've been coming here or 6 months and it's been a decent experience. The facility is very clean (incredibly cold so bring a jacket or blanket!) and the staff has been nice and patient when helping me, I have not received any rude staff members as others have complained about.

You will wait a few hours on your first visit, so go on a day where you have absolutely nothing planned because you can wait from 4-6 hours although they tell you 2-4. Also, they can and will disqualify you for issues as small as asthma. So, ASK them first if you have medical issues before waiting so long. I've seen so many angry people scream and run out that door because they were disqualified after HOURS of waiting. ASK FIRST BEFORE WAITING!

Now Complaints...
They do seem understaffed on some days. The line will be going out the door which I really don't mind, it's when I'm finished that it's irritating. There were days where everyone would be finished at different times, and holding their hand up in their air ready leave for 20 minutes+ before staff came around. By then, EVERYONE begins to shout and claim that they were done first and whoever is the loudest or the closest to that staff member wins the game. If they had more staff members on the floor or even a number system instead of the hand raising thing, it would be less hostile and easier for both the donor and staff member.

My other complaint is some of the donors who go there. I've dealt with some short tempered hostile donors who try to fight for their place in line or fight to get unhooked from the IV and leave first, sometimes with me and sometimes with the staff. For the most part people are respectful but some of them are cranky and impatient and treat this place like it's there to only SERVE THEM but there's not really any way to avoid 'em.!</review>< pics>
None< /pics>

<Rating>5<//Rating><text>I have been donating at Octapharma regularly for about 4-6 months now. My time spent there has been a largely enjoyable experience. The staff is friendly and courteous, and this really says something considering how over-worked they are.

They could use more phlebotomists, but the ones there really know their stuff. And if you find a tech that you really like, they actually let you make requests. So if your favorite needle wizard is on duty, don‚Äôt be afraid to ask for their services.

Their registration while lengthy is actually streamlined so once you return the process goes much faster. This is of course all required by law and anyone criticizing them for this part of the procedure is simply ignorant of the fact that the staff & management cannot change this. Yes they are going to be collecting some very personal information, and yes some of your answers or a combination of them may disqualify you from donating‚Ä¶ Boo hoo.

This is not a retail service; you are not entitled to customer satisfaction. It is the staff‚Äôs foremost concern to protect the well being of their clients, and those who may be receiving donated plasma. For that reason they have to calculate the risk or chance that you may have some kind of disqualifying condition. Maybe your blood pressure is too low, too high, or maybe you engaged in & admitted to certain high risk behaviors. Either way, no one should be throwing daggers at an organization for complying with safety laws.

Wait times can be pretty long, but they are honest and forthright about this, telling every new customer that they can expect it to take between 2 and 3 hours. This is again, due to a lack of phlebotomists, and the popularity of this location. They are routinely swamped, with lines of beds full of people waiting their turn to get stuck. This is yet another thing that they as the company cannot control. They cannot wave a magical wand and produce a new tech with the same astounding level of skill I‚Äôve come to expect, nor can they banish the crowds of people that show up every day.

So yes the service, entirely because of circumstance, may be a little slow, but the quality is amazing.

The facilities are, well, unremarkable, but what do you expect, it‚Äôs a donation center. But it‚Äôs always very clean, and there are televisions positioned all around so you can always see one from any bed.

Their movie selection could use some serious, serious improvement however.<//text><Pics>None< /Pics>< Resp>

So, my new range wouldn't just slide in to the wall but leave a 3"gap behind the range - not acceptable. The solution - having to move a gas line. I am a DIY guy but prefer not to blow myself or my family up when dealing with gas, so had to call the professionals.

Called Dutton at 1:51 pm on a Monday and they had Steve, their gas specialist, out at my house before 4:00 pm. He and his apprentice looked at, accessed and gave me options for my repair/fix. It was ultimately going to take more time than completing it the same day. So, we were Steve's first appointment the following day. He was prompt, polite and professional. <user_id>103039532328897954247< /user_id><user_name>T H< /user_name>< time>
1598988729165<//time>
<rating>1<//rating>< Review>
I had a simple leaking faucet like most people do so I called Dutton Plumbing in Santa Clarita. When the service tech arrived, I explained the problem and symptoms of the leak and showed him that when I applied light downward pressure to the hot water handle, the drip would stop. This guy, without ever looking under the sink or taking the water handle off to inspect the fixture told me that my entire faucet fixture would have to be rebuilt and replace the shut off valves under the sink or only replace the valves. Without inspecting the valves or the faucet itself, he gave a quote for $515 for replacing the valves and $795 for rebuilding the faucet and replacing the valves, both of which I declined as the cost seemed unusually high.

I emailed the company that manufactured the faucet and provided the exact same description of the problem via email that I gave Dutton Plumbing‚Äôs service tech in person. The faucet manufacturer replied back suggesting that I replace the seats and springs under the faucet handle and provided me with the part number. I purchased a two pack of the part for $4.98 and a tube of silicone grease for $4.00 at Home Depot and installed them myself in 10 minutes, resulting in the leak being fixed.

Dutton Plumbing not only misdiagnosed how to fix the leak, they suggested work that did not EVEN need to be done at the cost of nearly $800. They do this stuff for a living, so how could they not EVEN suggest replacing the seats and springs? But instead, he told me that I need to replace my entire faucet fixture and valve handles. I don't like being cheated and that is exactly what this place tried to do to me.

DO NOT let them do any work until you get a second opinion and estimate. They wanted to charge me $800 for work that did not need to be done AT ALL and I ended up fixing the leak myself and it literally cost me LESS THAN the price of a movie ticket. Read the Yelp reviews and you'll see a pattern of them trying to overcharge people.

I spoke to someone at the Dutton after they saw my review and he tried to make up an excuse, saying that they might suggest repairs that are "more comprehensive." There's a big difference between "more comprehensive" and repairs that are not required AT ALL. Crooks!</Review>

< review>
Amazing. Will use again if needed. I used the CHAT service on their webpage. It was a call center, but, I shortly received a call from Tania at the company. She explained it was a Sunday, and had one driver handling emergencies. She let me know that I would be in the queue and she would keep me updated. First appointment was 1100 am. I received a call postponing it to 200 pm. Shortly after, they called back and said Randy was on his way. He arrived a 11:15, well within when he was expected.

Randy was personal and professional. He was clean and polite. We were even able to make small talk without distracting his work. Not only was the visit quick, but no shady upset tactics. I paid $73,00 as advertised. He had to cut tree roots out of a line outside of the house with one of his tools. Not only did I get great service, I received great value.

With any other company, I would have paid 2-3 times what he charged.< /review>

I had a simple clog that couldn't be resolved with a bladder or consumer-grade auger. Heard good things about these guys from a friend, so I called. My call was answered by someone who spoke english, and was able to confirm a time to call me back to set an exact appointment time (same day). I didn't get a call back initially, so I called and rescheduled for the following day as I could not wait at home any longer. After that, smooth sailing. The dispatcher called me that next morning confirming a time, and then the repair man called me when he got there. He was cool enough to wait a few minutes for my fiance to get there. It took him 25 minutes to fix the clog and he was on his way. The price remained consistent, no surprises. This would have been 5 stars if I had initially gotten a call back like i was promised. However that being said, I would absolutely use these guys again.</Review>

<date>1412407909481< /date><rating>5< /rating><Text>I highly recommend this company if you need an honest accurate estimate for any plumbing problem. Everyone at Dutton Plumbing was very professional and curious.  I called for an estimate regarding a possible slab leak. The technicians arrived on time as scheduled.  I was greeted at my door by Matt; who immediately placed a clean mat on my door step, put on clean cover shoes over his work shoes. Matt accessed my situation very quickly entered my options with the exact cost on his iPad (which was very reasonable compared to other quotes I received). I opted for the slab fix..the by-pass option would also have fixed the hot water pipe leak in the slab. <Rate>5< /Rate>< review>
After having called numerous local plumbers who didn't bother to show up or even call back, I called Dutton Plumbing to fix an outdoor PVC pipe leak, and I couldn't be happier. Dan & Jake were 100% professionals and fixed the problem in 40 minutes. Even the dispatcher on their customer service line was helpful.

Ritz Plumbing tried and failed to fix the pipes 5 times in a row and - in fact, made the problem worse after each visit. After Ritz Plumbing gave up (and tried to extort additional money for warranty work), Dutton Plumbing was there to pick up the pieces AND show me exactly what negligence and shoddy workmanship caused my the leak in the first place.

Dan & Jake were knowledgeable, experienced, and more than helpful with their explanations and suggestions. They showed up ON TIME and within hours of being called. They even stayed on for an extra hour or so after the job was completed so they could test that the leak was indeed corrected. Dutton Plumbing warrants the work for 1 year after the visit and as Dan put it: "We will own our mistakes and not charge you extra."  Too bad more companies aren't like this.</review>

I had quite a lot of plumbing work done ( replaced 2 toilets, 2 sinks/ vanities, new kitchen faucet, and replaced main sewer line out to the street.). My only problem was with dispatch, who did not seem to comprehend the scope of the work being done on a house built in the 1950's. Dispatch often would schedule Jay to come at 5pm, and he wouldn't be able to make it, as he was on another job and couldn't make it. I am a young, single mother and Dutton's technicians basically tried to rob me. A 5 or 6 inch piece of exposed PVC pipe between two connectors on my sprinkler valve broke. I called Dutton and they sent their technician Matt out with another tech (not sure why they sent TWO people when I told them it was literally just a piece of PVC that needed to be removed and replaced). If I knew how to deal with the blue PVC cement I would have fixed the damn thing myself. So Matt and tech 2 show up and tell me "Oh, yeah that's an easy fix. We'll just have to dig around it a little bit and I'll charge you the exposed rate so it won't be as much for you." Tech 2 is in the grass kicking a soccer ball around with my daughter. They're really laying it on thick getting my guard down. So... now it comes time for them to rig up the invoice and get my signature... $450!!! Are you kidding me?! At first, because I have no idea what I'm doing, I was going to agree to it. Thankfully my roommate got home in the nick of time and told them that we would get a second opinion. My father came by and fixed it in less than 10 minutes. Dutton was going to rob a young, single mother of $450 for a $5 piece of PVC, some PVC cement, and 7 minutes of labor. How could anyone be so heartless and money hungry?< /Text>

<Rating>1</Rating>< Review>
All I can say is... GET A SECOND OPINION!! ... I had 1 bath room with  a clogged sink and toilet.. They said my pipes were broke under the house and the one pipe in front was cracked.. They said I needed ALL new plumbing at a cost of $12,000.00.. I questioned this because the rest of my plumbing was working fine.. I said I thought $12,000.00 was slightly extreme and their answer was "Well we do financing"  They never showed me any pictures or video that was used during the inspection.. I told them no thank you and without any other options from them, they left.. I called another company who came with their camera and showed me that the main entrance where he used his camera had not even been opened due to it being covered with dirt and spider webs. He then had me watch the video of the inside of my plumbing (amazing btw..) to show me no broken pipes but areas where there was settling that was causing pooling and due to build up, caused the clogs.. He flushed out the pipes with a hydro hose and viola... no clogs.. Oh and there was NO cracked pipes in the front either.. He was gracious enough to show me everything that he was doing so that I could understand..He charged me $625.00... I don't know if that is a good or bad price for what he did but, I do know it is a far cry from $12,000.00..  Shame on you Dutton Pluming !! If I could give you 0 stars I would!!< /Review>

<Rating>5<//Rating>< review>
Danny D and Leo B provided service for our residence on a leaking faucet and water pressure regulator. Danny was the main technician and Leo assisted him. Danny was very knowledgable, professional, courteous and friendly. He took time to explain the problem to us, how he planned to approach remedying it and the relative costs. As for expertise and professionalism, their service was excellent. I was especially pleased by Dan's positive professional demeanor. They were prompt, finished the work within the quoted timeframe, explained their process beforehand so we knew exactly what services we were receiving, and they left their workspace as clean as they found it. As for cost, we have worked with less expensive plumbers in the past, so Dutton is not the most competitive provider in terms of pricing, however with Dan's professionalism and a very organized business service model (we have not experienced a more organized effort, from front office to completion), customers can reasonably expect to pay a bit more than what a sole provider/owner-operator would charge that doesn't offer such a comprehensive service model, which includes your initial call, prompt scheduling, phone updates, e-mail updates and accurate time estimations for both technician arrival and work performance. We might have been able to shop around for a cheaper solution since this call was not an emergency call, but overall, we feel we have received value for our dollar.<//review>

I have been a faithful customer of Dutton for over 15 years.  Thursday night around 9pm I entered my garage only to find my hot water heater leaking water. I could not wait and had to search for another plumber in the yellow pages.  Another came to my rescue and turned off the water heater, disconnected the gas line after turning it off and drained the tank of the remaining water. He then called DWP to have them come turn the water back on, and, since he could not test the new valve he installed, Jake showed me how to check it.  He said if there was any leakage to call him and he would come right back and fix any problems.  I know the complication with the city's valve made extra work for him, but I was not charged any additional fee, and he got me a $50 discount coupon because I called after meeting Dutton Plumbing at Starbucks.  I could not be more satisfied for the professionalism that Jake demonstrated, and his willingness to see the job through no matter what extra time or inconvenience arose due to outside complications.  Without reservation, I extend my highest recommendation for Dutton Plumbing because of the outstanding service that Jake provided.<//Text>< pics>

<rate>1< /rate>< Text>
Called Dutton office at 7:00 AM, they said someone would be there between 9-11, no problem, then got call saying they would be there in 30 mins, they showed up almost 45 mins, again no problem.

The plumbing problem was a broken PVC pipe in the Meter box, easy to get to.  Well my Father was a plumber and I spent many years helping, so I know whats involved, this is a 15 minute, job 20 if you run into roots.  The guys showed up from Dutton in a nice new van, in pristine white shirts, carrying what looks like a doctors bag. I tried not to laugh out loud, wondering if they realized they were plumbers not doctors.  I told them they would not need all that its a simple pipe repair.   They then took about 10 mins to write up a estimate which was $816.00, but he was very proud that he was able to save me $134.00 and that's how he got it down to $816.00.  I told him he must be mistaken.  When he looked at me as if i was stupid I told him to take his fancy bag get back in his truck and get out of here.  That I am happy to pay a fair price but that was ridiculous and that I hope they don't rip everyone off in the same manner.

BTW Gordan Taylor Plumbing came out right away did the job in about 15 mins.  and I had him tend to a few other issues I had been meaning to fix like my R/O filter system under my sink, check my pressure regulator, test the pressure on the house, check a gas line to my fire pit. WOW I am sure when Dutton would add these other items I would have to take a loan out on the house to pay their bill.  BTW Gordon Taylor Plumbing did the whole job for under $200.00.

The odd thing is the guy from Dutton did not even seem surprised at my response I guess he hears it often.  I never got a call back trying to explain or appologize.  I realize companies are allowed to charge what they like, but at rates like that I am fearful for the people who don't know any better.  I had heard of a senior citizen who had them change a water heater for nearly $3,000.00 and I dismissed it as urban legend as that was just crazy pricing and who would pay such an amount, but now i must wonder if this was a myth.  I have been told their Plumbers work on a commissions.

I have used Dutton before and they were expensive, but this time they were crazy.  They have lost my business and have earned a special place as I will tell everyone of my experiences.  I wonder how many people they actually take advantage of like this.</Text>
